Beyond prompting, an established technique to obtain CSK assertions is supervised learning based on LMs. We adapted the COMET-ATOMIC-2020 system [hwang2020comet], which in turn is based on the GPT-2 LM. Like the previous prompt-based extraction, the core component is a pre-trained LM, which we can fine-tune on different text corpora. Compared to the previous method, however, a relation-specific step of supervised learning is added, in which the model is trained to generate objects for given subject-relation pairs.